#4841;&#4961; &#4640;&#4653;&#4672;&#4961; &#4620;&#4618;&#4725;&#4961; &#4978;&#4808;&#4973;&#4961; &#4632;&#4819;&#4621;&#4721;&#4962; &#4824;&#4720;&#4643;&#4840;&#4902; &#4704;&#4757;&#4811;&#4841; &#4978;&#4808;&#4970; &#4709;&#4653;&#4962; &#4824;&#4640;&#4648;&#4678; &#4808;&#4824;&#4936;&#4608;&#4678; &#4813;&#4873;&#4824; &#4616;&#4845;&#4777;&#4757; &#4704;&#4645;&#4621;&#4899;&#4752; &#4916;&#4901;&#4654;&#4661; &#4808;&#4915;&#4813;&#4622;&#4661;&#4962;</span></span></p><foreign xml:lang="en"><p><span unicode="" style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;Arial">Fol. 1va: This book is of T&#228;w&#228;ld&#228; M&#228;d&#7723;&#1241;n that he gave to Maryam K&#228;dih. The name of his wife is W&#228;l&#228;tt&#228; &#704;Anan&#1241;ya, his father is W&#228;ld&#228; Samu&#704;el, his mother is W&#228;l&#228;tt&#228; Haymanot, his son is G&#228;br&#228; Maryam, his daughters are W&#228;l&#228;tt&#228; &#346;&#1241;llase, W&#228;l&#228;tt&#228; Maryam, W&#228;l&#228;tt&#228; T&#1241;n&#347;a&#704;e and his brothers are W&#228;ld&#228; Abraha, G&#228;br&#228; &#704;Anan&#1241;ya, Kidan&#228; Maryam. It was written in the year of Mathew, during the reign of King Yo&#7717;ann&#1241;s and (the time of) g&#228;b&#228;z K&#1241;fl&#228; &#7716;awaryat in 1877 year of mercy in the month of Y&#228;katit (= 22 February 1885 A.D.) &#8230;</span></p></foreign>
